data.text:
Goose and Iceman are heading to Maverick’s to put Pizza 73’s wings to the test. They pride themselves on a golden crispy wing, but how will they fare on opening night? Join us this week from the couch, as we bring you our first take out wing review!

The Stats.

Wing Night!

None. Maybe you should give us a break, Pizza 73.

Flavours (8 for $7.99 | 20 for $15.99 | 40 for $29.99 | 80 for $49.99)

GOLDEN CRISPY | SCREAMIN’ HOT | BBQ | LEMON PEPPER | HONEY GARLIC | TERIYAKI | CHIPOTLE (breaded/not breaded) | BUFFALO (breaded/not breaded)

We tried Golden Crispy, Screamin’ Hot, Lemon Pepper, Teriyaki, Chipotle (Breaded), Buffalo (Breaded)

OVERALL RATING

7.333333333333333333/10

Our Verdict.

Pizza 73 will always hold a special place in our hearts, and the atmosphere was obviously tops at Maverick’s. The waitresses were damn fine and the beers flowed generously. Our delivery guy was right on time for the beginning of the Connor McDavid era.

I don’t understand why anyone would order anything but the golden crispies. Next time we will just do 80 of those – Maverick.

Overall Rating: 7.5

Size Factor: 8

Crisp Factor: 6

Juicy Factor: 7

Flavour Factor: 8.5

Sauce/Seasoning Factor: 8

Value Factor: 5

Not much bang for the buck here but a convenient option. Depth of flavours could use some work. – Goose.

Overall Rating: 7.5

Pricy… but hey, you barely have to get off the couch! – Iceman.
